Article IV. City Clerk

ยง C-12. Qualifications; powers and duties.
[Amended 10-3-2002 by L.L. No. 8-2002]
The City Clerk shall be a resident elector of the City; selected by the City Council at its organizational meeting to hold office until the next organizational meeting unless sooner removed by a vote of 2/3 of the members of the Council. He/She shall attend all meetings of the Council, keep a journal of Council proceedings, and discharge such other duties as may be prescribed by law or ordinance. He/She shall be a commissioner of deeds and shall have custody of the City Seal. He/She may appoint deputies and assistants to hold office during his/her pleasure, with the approval of the City Council.
ยง C-13. Registrar of Vital Statistics.
[Amended by L.L. No. 5-1994, ยง 3]
There shall be a Registrar of Vital Statistics within the office of City Clerk. He/She shall be appointed by the Mayor for an indefinite term of office. Under the supervision and control of the Mayor, he/she shall maintain permanent records of all births and deaths occurring within the City. He/She shall record all stillbirths and issue burial permits.
ยง C-14. City Clerk to give bond.
The City Clerk, before exercising any of the powers or discharging any of the duties of the office, shall execute a bond to the City in such sum as the City Council may direct by ordinance, and with such sureties as the Council may approve, conditioned for the faithful performance of the duties and the office, and that he/she may properly apply and account for all public money and all public property received by him/her. Such bond may be a blanket bond covering all employees of the City required to be bonded, whichever the Council may decide. Such bond shall be filed in the office of the Clerk of the County of Rensselaer and by him/her recorded at length in a book kept for the purpose of recording the bonds of City officers.
